<h1>Poem and Quotes on Kindness</h1>
 </header>
 <section id="main">
<article>
<h2>Send a Drop of Kindness</h2>
<h3>Poet: <cite>Julie Hebert</cite></h3>
<p>
Send a drop of <strong>kindness</strong>,<br />
And see a <em>happy face</em>.<br />
A drop of kindness goes real far,<br />
It may even reach outer space.</p>
<p>Send a drop of <strong>love</strong>,<br />
And feel a <em>loving embrace</em>.<br />
It feels so good to feel like,<br />
You are in the right place.</p>
<p>Send a drop of <strong>hope</strong>,<br />
But be that <em>shinning star</em>.<br />
Hope is wonderful to have,<br /> 
But sometimes you can't sit away so far.</p>
<p>Send a drop of <strong>faith</strong>,<br />
With a <em>single prayer</em>.<br />
And God will show the way,<br />
As faith is always there.</p>
</p>
</article>
<hr />
<article>
<h2>Quotes on Kindness</h2>
<blockquote cite="http://www.wow4u.com/">
<p>"No act of kindness, no matter how small is ever wasted." --
<cite>Aesop</cite></p>
<p>"The love, kindnesses, and value we have given authentically
to others will be our remaining treasures at the end of life. --
<cite>Steve Brunkhorst</cite></p>
<p>"You will never have a completely bad day if you show kindness
at least once." -- <cite>Greg Henry Quinn</cite></p>
</article>
